headline: Motorola Solutions forecasts weak second-quarter profit amid tariff uncertainty
summary: Safety and enterprise security services provider Motorola Solutions forecast second-quarter profit below Wall Street estimates on Thursday. Shares of the Chicago, Illinois-based company fell about 5% in extended trading. "As a result of the dynamic environment, the company expects increased costs on materials and components in 2025, which the company currently expects to substantially mitigate," Motorola Solutions said.
